## Key Research References

| Paper | Relevance to Glassbox |
|---|---|
| **SRBench** (La Cava et al., 2021) | Calibrated priors + strong constant optimization = top quartile |
| **PySR** (Cranmer, 2023) | BFGS inner loop, adaptive parsimony, Pareto selection |
| **Operon** (Burlacu et al., 2020) | Levenberg-Marquardt for constant optimization — gold standard |
| **PIGP** (Jha et al., NeurIPS 2024) | Seeding GP with Transformer candidates → 2-5× speedup |
| **eggp / EGG-SR** (Kronberger et al., 2025) | E-graph deduplication to eliminate wasted evaluations |
| **AI Feynman 2.0** (Udrescu & Tegmark, 2020) | Separability/symmetry tests for multivariate decomposition |
| **StruSR** (2025) | Sensitivity-guided mutation (protect good subtrees) |

---

## Expected Impact

If Phases 1-3 are executed well, based on the research baselines:

| Metric | Current (v3.1) | Projected |
|---|---|---|
| Exact recovery rate | 59% (121/205) | ~70-75% |
| Runtime (full suite) | 1967s | ~1400-1600s |
| Structural-correctness rate | ~70% | ~85% |
| Hard-composition recovery | ~30% | ~45-50% |

The biggest jump will come from **LM constant optimization** (ADD 1) and **formula-honest selection** (ADD 2) — these directly attack the two largest failure categories identified in `limitations.md`.
